      "content": "Let's start with the basics. Modern civilizations are typically characterized by the presence of a dominant, often white, ruling class, whereas primitive societies are often marked by a more egalitarian distribution of power and resources. Key markers of a civilization include the development of complex systems of governance, writing, and technology, as well as a strong emphasis on individualism and competition. In contrast, primitive societies tend to be more communal and focused on collective survival, often with a more fluid or matrilineal social hierarchy.",
